summary: This is an FBI FD-302 form documenting the receipt and initial processing of an Apple iPhone (evidence item 1844) for extraction. The device was submitted for a Full File System extraction via a Mobile Device Unlock Service Request (MDUS) as part of an investigation.

events.title: iPhone Received for Forensic Extraction
events.description: CART received one Gold/Black Apple iPhone, model A1920, as evidence item 1844 for extraction. An examination was started and a Mobile Device Unlock Service Request (MDUS) was submitted to the Electronic Device Analysis Unit (EDAU) for a Full File System extraction.

locations: New York, New York, United States
keyFacts: An Apple iPhone (model A1920, S/N: F17XD9PKKPFW, IMEI:357208091738649) was received as evidence item 1844 for forensic extraction on August 26, 2019.
The extraction was performed pursuant to a signed consent to search form dated August 26, 2019.
A Mobile Device Unlock Service Request (MDUS Number 10754) was submitted to the Electronic Device Analysis Unit (EDAU) for a Full File System extraction.
The document is an FBI FD-302 form related to investigation 90A-NY-3151227 and file 321C-NY-A6382037-MOBILE.
The document contains a standard disclaimer that it is the property of the FBI, loaned to the receiving agency, and not to be distributed outside that agency.
